<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>PushEt</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0-wip/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0-rc2/css/bootstrap-glyphicons.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/3.0.2/css/font-awesome.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/startup%2Fcode%2Fsocial-buttons.css">
    <link href="http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ubuntu:300,400,500,700,300italic,400italic,500italic,700italic" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <link href="http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:300italic,400italic,600italic,700italic,300,400,600,700,800"
    rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery.js"></script>
    <script src="http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0-wip/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">
      $(document).ready(function() {
        transition();
        $("#carousel-examples").carousel('cycle');
      });
      var slidenum = 2;
      function transition() {
        $("#slideshow").attr('src', "img/slide" + slidenum + ".png");
        if (++slidenum > 3)
          slidenum = 2;
        window.setTimeout("transition()", 1000);
      }
    </script>
    <style type="text/css">
      /* Large desktop */
      @media (min-width: 980px) {
        body {
          padding-top: 60px;
        }
        .linediv-l {
          border-right: 1px white solid;
        }
        .linediv-r {
          border-left: 1px white solid;
        }
      }

      /* Landscape phones and down */
      @media (max-width: 480px) {
        .copy {
          padding: 2.5% 10%;
        }
        .linediv-l {
          border-bottom: 1px white solid;
        }
        .linediv-r {
          border-top: 1px white solid;
        }
      }

      /* All form factors */

      /* Main body and headings */
      body {
        font-family: 'Open Sans', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      }
      .heading, .subheading {
        font-family: 'Ubuntu', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .subheading {
        box-shadow: 0px 1px 3px 0px #acacac;
        background: #fcfcfc;
      }
      p.lead {
        padding-top: 1.5%;
        font-size: 24px;
        line-height: 30px;
      }
      p {
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 24px;
      }

      /* Video pitch and Action */
      .pitch {
        padding: 2.5% 0%;
      }
      .order {
        padding: 2% 0%;
      }
      .actions {
        background-color: #343434;
        padding: 3% 0%;
      }
      .video, .thermometer, .order, .social, .statistics {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .statistics h3, .statistics p {
        color: white;
      }

      /* Marketing Copy and Footer */
      .copy {
        padding-top: 2.5%;
        padding-bottom: 2.5%;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      .asset {
        padding: 2.5% 0%;
      }
      footer {
        color: #cccccc;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 1%;
      }
      footer p {
        font-size: 11px;
      }
      footer a {
        color: #ccccff;
      }
      div.addthis_toolbox {
        width: 180px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top bs-docs-nav" role="banner">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="navbar-header">
          <button class="navbar-toggle" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".bs-navbar-collapse">
            <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          </button>
          <a href="/" class="navbar-brand">PushEt</a>
        </div>
        <nav class="collapse navbar-collapse bs-navbar-collapse" role="navigation">
          <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
            <li class="active">
              <a href="/">Home</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#about">About</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#plan">Plan</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#benefits">Benefits</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="row text-center">
        <img src="img/logo.png" alt="PushEt">
      </div>
      <div class="row subheading">
        <p class="lead">
          Press a physical button from anywhere in the world
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row pitch">
        <div class="col-md-6 video">
          <img class="img-thumbnail" id="slideshow" src="img/slide1.png" alt="PushEt Pitch">
        </div>
        <% var backers = 0; var bc_sum = 0; %>
        <% for(var i=0; i<orders.length; i++) {%>
        <% backers = backers + 1 %>
        <% bc_sum = bc_sum + orders[i].amount %>
        <% } %>

        <div class="col-md-6 actions">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row statistics">
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="linediv-l">
                  <h3><%=backers %></h3>
                  <p>
                    backers
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="linediv-c">
                  <h3>
                  <%= bc_sum %> 
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    coins raised
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="linediv-r">
                  <h3 id="countdown">100</h3>
                  <p>
                    days left
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
                <div class="thermometer progress active">
                  <div class="bar bar-success" style="width: <%= (bc_sum / 20) * 100 %>%;"></div>
                  <div class="bar bar-warning" style="width: <%= 100 - (bc_sum / 20) * 100 %>%;"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row order">
              <div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
                <a class="coinbase-button" data-code="e85ae87599b3a91d34411400c36621bc" data-button-style="custom_large" data-button-text="Preorder 0.2 Bitcoins" data-button-style="custom_small" href="https://coinbase.com/checkouts/e85ae87599b3a91d34411400c36621bc"> Preorder 0.2 Bitcoins</a>
                <script src="https://coinbase.com/assets/button.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row social">
              <div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-2">
                <div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style addthis_32x32_style">
                  <a class="addthis_button_preferred_1"></a>
                  <a class="addthis_button_preferred_2"></a>
                  <a class="addthis_button_compact"></a>
                  <a class="addthis_counter addthis_bubble_style"></a>
                </div>
                <script type="text/javascript">
                  var addthis_config = {
                    "data_track_addressbar" : true
                  };
                </script>
                <script type="text/javascript"
                src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-51fc74f223a1b2ae"></script>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row section0" id="about">
        <div class="jumbotron">
          <h1>What Is It?</h1>
          <p>
            A small device affixed to any physical button, which is controllable via WiFi.
          </p>
          <p>
            It is a prototype in working. The basic idea is that not everything has been connected to the internet, but now almost everything could be. The PushEt&trade; device operates by remotely pressing a button for you using internet connected devices such as your phone, tablet, or computer at your convenience. You could even set it up on a timer to do it automatically for you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row section1" id="plan">
        <div class="col-md-6 copy pull-left">
          <div class="jumbotron">
            <h1>The Plan</h1>
            <p>
              Using some basic off the shelf parts, a remote device can leverage the battery to trigger a solenoid for pressing the button. The ideal napkin drawing calls for using a silicone mold which would contain the control circuitry (something that can detect wireless signals such as WiFi), a battery to last a few months of normal use, and a solenoid to do the actual pressing. By leveraging a good design, the silcone could also allow the user to manually press the button.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 asset pull-right">
          <img class="img-thumbnail" src="img/device.png" alt="PushEt Device">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row section2">
        <div class="col-md-6 asset pull-left">
          <div id="carousel-examples" class="carousel slide">
            <ol class="carousel-indicators">
              <li data-target="#carousel-examples" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
              <li data-target="#carousel-examples" data-slide-to="1" class=""></li>
              <li data-target="#carousel-examples" data-slide-to="2" class=""></li>
              <li data-target="#carousel-examples" data-slide-to="3" class=""></li>
            </ol>
            <div class="carousel-inner">
              <div class="item active">
                <img src="img/coffee.png" alt="PushEt For Coffee Makers">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                  <h3>Coffee Makers</h3>
                  <p>
                    Set up a timer, turns an old coffee maker into a new one
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="item text-center">
                <img src="img/microwave.png" alt="PushEt For Microwaves">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                  <h3>Microwaves</h3>
                  <p>
                    Stop the beeping from your couch
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <img src="img/light.png" alt="PushEt For Lights">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                  <h3>Lights</h3>
                  <p>
                    On and off from anywhere in the world
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <img src="img/remote.png" alt="PushEt For Remotes">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                  <h3>Remotes</h3>
                  <p>
                    Basically anything, even remotes themselves
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a class="left carousel-control" href="#carousel-examples" data-slide="prev"> <span class="icon-prev"></span> </a>
            <a class="right carousel-control" href="#carousel-examples" data-slide="next"> <span class="icon-next"></span> </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 copy pull-right">
          <div class="jumbotron">
            <h1>Examples</h1>
            <p>
              With an adhesive backing, the device can be connected to anything.
            </p>
            <p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Ever wish you can remotely power on/off your computer?
                </li>
                <li>
                  Ever wish you could just stop the microwave from the couch?
                </li>
                <li>
                  What about switch the lights on an off while you are away?
                </li>
              </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
              The PushEt&trade; device connects to anything it can press, make analog devices digital.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row section3" id="benefits">
        <div class="jumbotron">
          <h1>Final Benefits</h1>
          <p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Apply ontop of existing parts to add internet connectivity
              </li>
              <li>
                As simple as it gets, single functionality. Once setup - no training to use
              </li>
              <li>
                Entirely re-usable. Put it on something else if you don't need it anymore
              </li>
              <li>
                Secure connection, only you or a delegate can press the button (no one needs to know to what)
              </li>
              <li>
                Timer functionality, can press on your schedule
              </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row section4">
        <div class="jumbotron">
          <h1>Status</h1>
          <p>
            The idea is currently a napkin drawing turning into a large scale test. Having backers and funding would allow research and development to shrink the prototype down, as well as validate the need in the market for such a device.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row faq" id="faq">
        <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
          <h3>FAQ</h3>
          <div class="panel-group" id="accordian">
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span><a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"
                data-parent="#accordian" href="#collapseOne"> What would the funding provide? </a></h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                  With enough backers the idea would validated for market potential. All that would remain is leverage large scale manufacturing to take the small parts and integrate them into the desired housing.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span><a class="panel-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"
                data-parent="#accordian" href="#collapseTwo"> How is it controlled? </a></h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                  The early prototypes would run a simplified webserver on the device itself, with just 1 big button. The idea is to finalize the device by using a centralized webserver so that it can run offline for security and timer functionality.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span><a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"
                data-parent="#accordian" href="#collapseThree"> How is it powered? </a></h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                  Using regular coin cell batteries. No testing has been on how many button presses can be conducted, but the goal is to have it last a few months under normal use.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span><a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"
                data-parent="#accordian" href="#collapseFour"> How big is it? </a></h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                  The intent is to be small enough to cover a button on a remote, though early prototypes are far too big. Two designs exists:
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      The one depicted <a href="#plan">above</a> where all the elements are self contained
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      The solenoid is connected via an external power and control circuitry
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  The second design allows for a smaller footprint that gets close to covering a single button plus a few millimetres for adhesive backing.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel">
              <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span><a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse"
                data-parent="#accordian" href="#collapseFive"> When can it be ready? </a></h4>
              </div>
              <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                  Estimated to be Summer 2014. To manufacture enough pieces, there would be several iterations of design coupled with production. Early prototypes should be ready within 6 months (earlier if I quit my day job :P ).
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
    <footer>
      <p class="text-center">
        This work is under development and under copyright of the owner. No distribution allowed.
      </p>
    </footer>

  <script type="text/javascript">
    jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
      today = new Date();

